poem feedback warning i wrote it when i was really angry so you have to ignore some of it down can they not see what they do can they not feel my pain i can't sustain this longing call me mad for i'm not sane call me dumb call me foolish and i will doubt and i will wonder and you will win you always do you will win hear the thunder feel the rain i'm not me i'm the droplet falling down i am the thunder bolting life i am but a silent sound and when it speaks it's always right always right i'm always right because perfection won't let you down or would that also let you down always watching never being yet the fire is still burning are you seeing it's still burning and it won't stop until you're bleeding so bring me down and i'll fetch your crown but i won't kneel down i won't kneel down well done i'm an english teacher and i like it i like the imagery and symbolism lots of contrasted issues and a great theme dealing with an emotional issue gonna give you a star since i can't give you a good grade Similarities between the Bible and the Qur'an Treehouse of Horror V Episodes of Lost (Season 1) Four Quartets Sin City Thunderstorm Phoneme The Marshall Mathers LP Poker jargon C. S. Lewis Taikyoku shogi Empire Burlesque Dionysus Second language acquisition Otello Star Wars Episode III: Revenge of the Sith Fire fighting Bob Dylan Obi-Wan Kenobi DDRMAX2: Dance Dance Revolution Steve Reich True Crime: Streets of LA Burning Man Jon Secada W.I.T.C.H. K' Blood on the Tracks Desire (album) Piccolo Junior Saga The Ashes Criticisms of Charismatic and Pentecostal belief Storytelling Goodness and value theory Church of Jesus Christ of Latter-day Saints Saul Bellow The Dunciad Stan (song) Final Fantasy magic Alfred Korzybski Waking the Dragons Hulk (comics) Rush Limbaugh Past teachings of Prem Rawat Balthasar G__rard Autism Literature of the United States Son Gohan Buddy Guy USS Tunny (SS-282) The Ashlee Simpson Show Force (Star Wars) Sant Thakar Singh Pok__mon Live! EastEnders Tina Tur